-- Egypt's EGPC Agrees to Join Zubair Project in Iraq, Eni Chief Scaroni Says
-- Tommaso Ebhardt
-- 2010-07-12T13:57:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/egypt-s-egpc-agrees-to-join-zubair-project-in-iraq-eni-chief-scaroni-says.html

          
          
             Egyptian General Petroleum Corp.,
the nation’s state-owned oil marketing company, will join Eni
SpA’s Zubair project in Iraq, Eni Chief Executive Officer Paolo
Scaroni said at a conference in Milan today.  
 Eni, Italy’s biggest oil company, will sign an agreement
with Egypt on July 21, Scaroni said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
